    <subsection xml:id="subsubsec-Using-the-Compound-Interest-Formula">
        <title>Using the Compound Interest Formula</title>
        
        <p>
            <alert>Compound interest Formula:</alert>
            <me>
                F = P \left(1 + \dfrac{r}{n} \right)^{nt}
            </me>
        </p>

        
     
        <p>
            If you have seen this content before, you may be more familiar with a different notation: let <m>i = \dfrac{r}{n}</m>, <m>m = nt</m>, then
            <me>F = P (1 + i)^{m}</me>. You should feel free to use this notation if you are more comfortable with it, but it will not be given in the examples in the text. 
        </p>
       
